---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Christopher de Beer">
	<main class="content-container">
		<header class="intro">
			<h1>Christopher de Beer</h1>
			<p class="subtitle">Citizen of the web</p>
		</header>
		
		<section class="garden-welcome">
			<p>This is a digital garden—a space where ideas grow organically through exploration and connection. Unlike traditional websites with rigid hierarchies, here thoughts and <a href="/projects/">experiments</a> interweave naturally, revealing patterns and relationships through the process of making and writing.</p>
			
			<p>You might begin by following <a href="/blog/">ongoing thoughts</a> as they develop, exploring the <a href="/tags/">emergent themes</a> that arise through sustained inquiry, or wandering through various <a href="/projects/">explorations and experiments</a> that capture different moments of curiosity and discovery.</p>
			
			<p>The structure you encounter isn't predetermined—it has grown through the accumulation of ideas and their natural connections. Each link strengthens the web of understanding, creating new pathways for exploration and serendipitous discovery.</p>
		</section>
		
		<section class="garden-meta">
			<h2>About This Garden</h2>
			<p>This space embodies the principles of digital gardening: organic growth over rigid organization, connection over categorization, exploration over consumption. The design follows Edward Tufte's emphasis on clean typography and readability, letting ideas take center stage.</p>
			
			<p>Every page connects to others through contextual linking and automatic backlinks, creating a living web of knowledge that grows and evolves over time. This is thinking made visible—not as polished final products, but as ongoing development and discovery.</p>
		</section>
	</main>
</Layout>

<style>
	.intro {
		text-align: center;
		margin-bottom: 3rem;
		border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
		padding-bottom: 2rem;
	}
	
	.intro h1 {
		font-size: 2.8em;
		margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
		font-weight: 400;
		color: var(--text-primary);
	}
	
	.subtitle {
		font-size: 1.2em;
		color: var(--text-secondary);
		font-style: italic;
		margin: 0;
	}
	
	.garden-welcome {
		margin-bottom: 3rem;
		padding: 2rem;
		background: var(--background-subtle);
		border-left: 3px solid var(--accent);
	}
	
	.garden-welcome p {
		font-size: 1.1em;
		line-height: 1.7;
		color: var(--text-primary);
		margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
	}
	
	.garden-welcome p:last-child {
		margin-bottom: 0;
	}
	
	.garden-welcome a {
		color: var(--accent);
		text-decoration: none;
		font-weight: 500;
	}
	
	.garden-welcome a:hover {
		text-decoration: underline;
	}
	
	.garden-meta {
		padding: 2rem 0;
		border-top: 1px solid var(--border-light);
	}
	
	.garden-meta h2 {
		font-size: 1.4em;
		margin: 0 0 1.5rem 0;
		font-weight: 400;
		color: var(--text-primary);
	}
	
	.garden-meta p {
		font-size: 1em;
		line-height: 1.6;
		color: var(--text-secondary);
		margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
	}
	
	.garden-meta p:last-child {
		margin-bottom: 0;
	}
	
	@media (max-width: 768px) {
		.intro h1 {
			font-size: 2.2em;
		}
		
		.subtitle {
			font-size: 1.1em;
		}
		
		.garden-welcome {
			padding: 1.5rem;
		}
		
		.garden-welcome p {
			font-size: 1em;
		}
		
		.garden-meta {
			padding: 1.5rem 0;
		}
		
		.garden-meta h2 {
			font-size: 1.2em;
		}
	}
</style>